Legal Calculus focuses on **practical, repeatable skills**, including:

- Drafting filings and structuring motions
- Writing Statements of Undisputed Facts (SUFs)
- Preserving evidence and documenting retaliation
- Preventing procedural dismissal
- Modeling timelines and tracking deadlines
- Understanding arbitration mechanics
- Tracking judicial silence
- Building an appeal‑ready record
- Using AI safely and procedurally

